channel.title: Class not found, but the class is there?

Yet the class [b]is[/b] there.

item.title: Class not found, but the class is there?
item.dc:creator: @Evil1 Evil_
item.description:
@Evil1 wrote:

[quote=“Echo_, post:12, topic:387779”]Don’t add the directory name to the code attribute, create a codebase attribute and add the directory name to that.[/quote]That’s not how it works when it’s a package like this. What that’s for is if the actual class isn’t located in the same directory, e.g. if you have them in a subdirectory bin/

I’ve actually made a quick applet to show all this, hopefully it can help out ranger_squad.

item.title: Class not found, but the class is there?
item.dc:creator: @Evil1 Evil_
item.description:
@Evil1 wrote:

Have you tried putting it in the actual folder hierarchy? e.g. org/jameskmonger/chatroom/client/ClientApplet.cass

And if it still doesn’t work, just jar it like you would a regular application, then put the jar where the html file is and load it like:

                <applet archive="ChatRoom.jar" code="org.jameskmonger.chatroom.client.ClientApplet" width=800 height=400>
                        <param name="host" value="127.0.0.1"/>
                        <param name="port" value="616"/>
                        <param name="name" value="james"/>
                </applet>
